                h3 1. Quantitative - Correlation with Business
                p 
                    | My first step was 
                    span.highlight justifying business impact
                    |  by investigating the correlation between converted users and their filtering behaviors.
                p
                    | As the graphs indicated, filtering behaviors from non-converted and converted users were not the same. On the one hand, users with stronger motivations were prone to interact with filters. On the other hand, for the group that applied any filter, the conversion rate was x% higher.
                p
                    | It showed the business value of filters as 
                    span.highlight they kept high intent users in the converting funnel
                    | .
                h3 2. Quantitative - Usability Indicators
                p I moved on to creating indicators that measured filters performance.
                p 
                    | Two fundamental indicators were sr_filter_shown and sr_filter_usage. One recorded how many users opened up the filters page while the other recorded how many users ended up applying filters. Additionally, I considered the difference between the two as 
                    span.highlight a signal that captured friction users experienced during the filtering process
                    | . The larger the difference, the worse the usability.
                p By comparing with the benchmark on mobile web, I found that filters were less frequently used and the cost was relatively high on apps.
                h3 3. Quantitative - Frequency of Use
                p I checked the applied frequency of various filter options. Undoubtedly the data was influenced by users segment and design solution, but it still inferred a general preference for prices, ratings, property types, and unique selling points from our existing users.
                h3 4. Qualitative - Guerrila Testing
                p
                    | On the qualitative side, I ran a 
                    span.highlight street testing
                    |  on a sample of 10, asking the participants to choose a stay for the forthcoming trip. 
                    span.highlight Merely interrupting, I was able to observe the most authentic user behaviors and evaluate usability closest to real situations.
                h3 5. Qualitative - Lab Study
                p
                    | As a next step, I conducted a 
                    span.highlight lab study
                    |  where participants performed filter-related tasks, compare with competitors, and finally give their thoughts about the overall experience. 
                    span.highlight Users were encouraged to think aloud and provide the most meticulous feedback. 
